Iraq ready to talk with U . S . - paper . The ruling Baath party newspaper al - Thawra said on Thursday Baghdad was prepared to open a dialogue with the United States . " Iraq realises quite well that the United States is a superpower with vital interests in the region . Iraq does not want to threaten these interests , " declared Thawra in a front - page editorial . " Iraq has no interest in fighting the United States or being hostile to it . It has more than one advantage in dealing with it , " the paper added . The paper said isolating or containing Iraq would not serve U . S . interests in the region . Washington leads a tough anti - Iraq camp at the U . N . Security Council . Iraq ' s President Saddam Hussein in remarks published on Wednesday called the United States the worst despot history had ever known . Thawra warned that Washington ' s " blind enmity " towards the government in Baghdad would eventually destroy its interests in the region . " If Iraq is not allowed to have a normal international way of life , enjoying security and stability , the region ' s security will remain under threat , without stability , " Thawra said . Thawra urged Washington to give up attempts to topple the Iraqi government . It said the 1991 Gulf War over Kuwait and the U . N . trade embargo had failed to change the regime . " The current ( U . S . ) administration , like its predecessor , has drastically failed in achieving its aims in the forefront of them the removal of the ruling regime in Iraq , " it said . Thawra said a dialogue with Iraq and the lifting of sanctions were the prerequisites for peace and stability in the area . 
